I love extending my personal cars to help others reach their destinations. I think peer to peer sharing is awesome, and I'm excited to host your trip! I know you will treat my cars with care while you enjoy an experience with no lines, no wait, and no hassle.

Please keep in mind that although our practices mimic rental car companies, Turo nor I claim to be a rental car company. Think of an actual rental car company as Amazon with 'new' and 'like new' inventory. While Turo is more like Ebay, where 'new' and 'like new' options may be available, but it's mostly pre-owned inventory.  Although my team and I do our best to be as proactive as possible, things can still occur. We ask for grace and patience as we manage multiple cars & trips, plus respond to incidents & messages daily.

A huge part of having a great experience is becoming familiar with the car you book so you have realistic expectations. You have the ability to ask questions to your host, review FAQs on the car's profile, google or YouTube features all prior to your trip start. I also provide real-time, pre-trip photos for you to review ahead of reaching the car so there are little to no surprises. If you find that you would like to change your selection upon reaching the car, you still have an opportunity to cancel your trip without moving the vehicle. Guests prematurely give poor ratings based on the inability to operate bluetooth features, confusion of seat controls, and even being confused as to how to exit the airport. 

As your host, I can not control anything related to the airport, but I am available for support as needed from start to finish of every trip.
